IncidentSuppNarrative.NarrativeText: On Monday, April 24, 2023 at approximately 1015 hours Members of the Kent County Task Force observed Robert Rashean Wright Jr. a black male (DOB: 08/24/1982) driving a gold in color Chrysler 300 bearing MD registration 1ET9728. Task Force member had prior knowledge that Robert Rashean Wright Jr. a black male (DOB: 08/24/1982) was currently wanted by Anne Arundel County Sheriffs Office for a Violation of Probation. Pfc. McGinnis of the Chestertown Police Department conducted a traffic stop of the gold in color Chrysler 300 bearing MD registration 1ET9728. The driver and sole occupant of the vehicle was identified as Robert Rashean Wright Jr. a black male (DOB: 08/24/1982). Wright Jr. was wanted through the Anne Arundel County Sheriffs Office for a Violation of Probation. Wright Jr. was placed under arrest for the warrant. Cpl. Walker and his K9 partner Oxan of the Chestertown Police Department and currently assigned to the Kent County Task Force, conduct an open-air sniff of the vehicle Wright Jr. was driving. McGinnis was advised by Cpl. Walker of Oxans alert to the odor of a narcotic, the vehicle Wright Jr. was driving. A search of the vehicle was conducted based off K9 Oxans alert. No illegal substances were located inside the vehicle. Wright Jr. had to be transported back to Anne Arundel County, MD for service of the warrant. Cpl. Walker transported Wright Jr. to the Anne Arundel County Detention Center located on Jennifer Rd. where Wright Jr. was transferred over to the custody of the AACSO. All events occurred in Chestertown, Kent County, Maryland. Cpl. Walker and Pfc. McGinnis body cameras were activated throughout this incident.
